The paper discusses the generalization of convolutional neural networks to Riemannian homogeneous manifolds, which are commonly encountered in diffusion magnetic resonance imaging. This makes it likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves theoretical generalization and proof of concept experiments, indicating that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Differential Geometry (cs.DG) sub-categories.
